{
  "guid": "spin",
  "name": "Three Pot",
  "description": "This algorithm allows you to run what are effectively DSP plug-ins, loaded from the MicroSD card. It was designed particularly to support programs written for the Spin Semiconductor FV-1 chip. The name Three Pot comes from the FV-1 hardware design all it has are stereo inputs and outputs, and connections for three pots for user controls. Although the focus is on converted FV-1 programs, the conversion works by translating the programs to C++ and then compiling them for the disting NT so you can if you like actually write C++ directly and use this algorithm to run it on the module.",
  "categories": [
    "DSP",
    "Plugin Loader",
    "FV-1",
    "Audio Processing"
  ],
  "short_description": "Runs DSP code from the SD card",
  "use_cases": [
    "Running FV-1 DSP programs",
    "Running custom C++ DSP code",
    "Eurorack module integration"
  ],
  "gui_description": "The UI for this algorithm is currently unique on the disting NT in that it not only provides a custom display, but it also changes the way the knobs work. Having three physical pots on the module, matched up to the three controls on each program, was just too good an opportunity to ignore. The display shows the program name, pot labels, and description all from the 3pot file if provided. The three pots on the module control the three pot parameters directly. Additionally, the right encoder changes the program.",
